Sundowns are 2-1 down from the first leg in Morocco though they did score a valuable away goal in the contest in Rabat. Anele Ngcongca was the goal-scorer in the tie. In addition, there were plenty of positive signs Downs' talented attack could give Wydad's defence plenty of problems. Feutmba, the 1998/99 Player's Player of the Season in South Africa, told Kickoff: "Even though we expected a better result, a draw or win, Sundowns still has a chance to go to the final. --News24--